PAYEE 15861 PRACTITIONER 00000  MESSAGE TO THE PAYEE
                  CORPORATE ACCOUNTING SYSTEM (CAS) UPGRADE
EFFECTIVE DECEMBER 8, 2024, PROCESSES THAT SUPPORT PAYMENT OF MSP CLAIMS
AND RECONCILIATION OF THE PROVINCE'S ACCOUNTS WILL BE UPGRADED.  THESE
CHANGES COMPLY WITH SECURITY STANDARDS SET BY THE OFFICE OF THE CHIEF
INFORMATION OFFICER (OCIO) TO ENSURE THE SECURITY OF CRITICAL FINANCIAL
FUNCTIONS.
SUBMISSION OF MSP AND PHARMANET CLAIMS WILL NOT CHANGE. THERE ARE NO CHANGES
TO REQUIREMENTS FOR ELECTRONIC MEDICAL RECORDS (EMR) VENDORS.  FOR CHEQUE
PAYMENTS:  CHEQUE NUMBER SEQUENCING WILL BE UPDATED FROM 8 DIGITS TO 11
DIGITS.  MSP CLAIM PAYMENTS ARE MADE ACCORDING TO THE MOST CURRENT MSP
PAYMENT SCHEDULE. FOLLOWING THE UPGRADE, PAYMENTS MAY BE REMITTED EARLIER
THAN DATES INDICATED IN THE SCHEDULE.  PUBLISHED DATES REMAIN THE
AUTHORIZED PAYMENT DATES AND SHOULD BE THE GUIDE FOR CLAIMS-RELATED
ACCOUNTING.

               UPDATE: ALPHANUMERIC CODE RANGE FOR MSP CLAIMS
TO ADDRESS THE PRACTITIONER AND PAYEE NUMBER SHORTAGE, MSP CLAIMS AND
TELEPLAN SYSTEMS TRANSITIONED TO ALPHANUMERIC CODES IN JUNE 2022.  THIS
CHANGE WAS PART OF THE PRACTITIONER AND PAYEE NUMBER SHORTAGE (PPNS) PROJECT
TO ENSURE ALL DOWNSTREAM SYSTEMS CAN ACCEPT ANY ALPHA CHARACTER
COMBINATIONS IN THOSE FIELDS.
AS OF JUNE 1, 2022, NEW PRACTITIONER/PAYEE CODES ARE ISSUED AS ALPHANUMERIC
VALUES, WITH 5 CHARACTERS STARTING WITH 'J' (E.G., J1234, J9876).  RECENT
PROJECTIONS COMPLETED BY THE MINISTRY OF HEALTH (MOH) INDICATE THAT FURTHER
EXPANSION IS NEEDED TO ACCOMMODATE THE INCREASED VOLUME OF DEMAND FOR NEW
PRACTITIONER AND PAYEE NUMBERS.
UPCOMING CHANGES:
TO EXPAND THE AVAILABILITY OF CODES, NEW PRACTITIONER/PAYEE NUMBERS WILL
START TO BE ASSIGNED WITH 'Q' AS THE INITIAL ALPHA CHARACTER (E.G., Q1234,
Q9876).  PLEASE BE ADVISED THAT THE FIRST CHARACTER PLACEMENT WITHIN THIS
FIELD WILL BE UPDATED TO ANOTHER ALPHA CHARACTER AGAIN IN FUTURE, AS NEEDED.
THERE WILL BE NO IMPACT TO THE FOLLOWING:
- PRACTITIONER OR PAYEE NUMBERS THAT HAVE ALREADY BEEN ISSUED.
- PRACTITIONER OR PAYEE NUMBERS WITHIN THE 90000 TO 99999 SERIES WILL
  REMAIN RESERVED AND WILL NOT BE DISTRIBUTED.
NO FURTHER ACTION IS REQUIRED FOR TELEPLAN VENDORS IF ALL NECESSARY SYSTEM
UPDATES FROM THE 2022 PPNS PROJECT HAVE BEEN SUCCESSFULLY DEPLOYED TO
ACCEPT ANY ALPHA CHARACTER COMBINATIONS IN THOSE FIELDS.
ACTION REQUIRED:
FOR TELEPLAN VENDORS WHO HAVE YET TO MAKE SYSTEMS CHANGES TO ACCOMMODATE
CHARACTERS OTHER THAN 'J', PLEASE BE ADVISED THAT SYSTEMS UPDATES MUST BE
IN PLACE BY MARCH 2025.
IF YOU HAVE QUESTIONS ABOUT THIS UPDATE OR THE SELECTION OF THE ALPHA
CHARACTER 'Q'; PLEASE CONTACT HIBC VIA ONE OF THE FOLLOWING OPTIONS:
BY PHONE:                                  BY FACSIMILE:
  VANCOUVER:          (604) 456-6950       (250) 405-3592
  ELSEWHERE IN B.C.:  1-866-456-6950
BY MAIL:
MEDICAL SERVICES PLAN
PO BOX 9480 STN PROV GOVT
VICTORIA, B.C.  V8W 9E7

              2023/24 BUSINESS COST PREMIUM FINAL RETRO PAYMENT
THE FINAL BUSINESS COST PREMIUM (BCP) RETROACTIVE PAYMENTS FOR THE 2023/24
FISCAL YEAR, WHICH INCLUDES PHYSICIANS REGISTERED UNDER THE EXPANDED
ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA, WILL BE DISBURSED BY HEALTH INSURANCE BC (HIBC) ON
DECEMBER 15, 2024.
PAYMENTS ON CLAIMS FOR DATES OF SERVICE BETWEEN APRIL 1, 2023, AND
MARCH 30, 2024, WILL APPEAR ON ELIGIBLE PHYSICIAN'S REMITTANCE STATEMENTS
UNDER ADJUSTMENT CODE BQ. PAYMENTS WILL VARY BETWEEN ELIGIBLE PHYSICIANS
AND BE LOWER FOR PHYSICIANS WHO HAVE ALREADY RECEIVED SOME, OR ALL, BCP
UNDER THE ORIGINAL 2019 PMA GUIDELINES.
FOR PHYSICIANS WHO ARE ELIGIBLE UNDER THE EXPANDED CRITERIA AND HAVE
COMPLETED THE BCP REGISTRATION PROCESS, DETAILS REGARDING THE RETROACTIVE
PAYMENT CALCULATIONS CAN BE FOUND AT:
HTTPS://WWW.DOCTORSOFBC.CA/MANAGING-YOUR-PRACTICE/COMPENSATION/BUSINESS-
COST-PREMIUM
ADDITIONALLY, DUE TO AUTOMATION CHALLENGES, THE CHANGES OUTLINED IN THE
2022 PMA WHICH EXPAND THE BCP TO HEALTH CARE SETTINGS OUTSIDE OF
COMMUNITY-BASED OFFICES ARE STILL DELAYED. CURRENTLY THE ONLY AUTOMATED
BCP PAYMENTS BEING PROCESSED AND PAID OUT ARE UNDER THE ORIGINAL 2019
PMA GUIDELINES. WE WILL CONTINUE TO UPDATE PHYSICIANS AS PROGRESS IS
MADE ON THE EXPANSION.
FOR TECHNICAL SUPPORT, REGISTRATION CONFIRMATION, AND QUESTIONS ABOUT BCP
PAYMENTS, PLEASE CONTACT HIBC DIRECTLY AT 1-866-456-6950. GENERAL QUESTIONS
REGARDING THE BCP CAN BE DIRECTED TO ECONOMICS@DOCTORSOFBC.CA
RETROACTIVE PAYMENTS ARE MADE TO THE PAYEE NUMBER ASSOCIATED WITH THE CLAIM
RECEIVING THE RETROACTIVE PAYMENT. PLEASE ENSURE THAT YOU HAVE UPDATED YOUR
BANKING INFORMATION FOR ALL YOUR PAYMENT NUMBERS. TO UPDATE YOUR BANKING
INFORMATION, COMPLETE A DIRECT BANK DEPOSIT FORM AND FAX TO (250) 405-3592.
THE DIRECT BANK DEPOSIT FORM CAN BE FOUND ON THE HIBC WEBSITE AT:
HTTP://WWW.GOV.BC.CA/MSPPHYSICIANS

                          AMEND FIS 13070 AND 13075
EFFECTIVE JANUARY 1, 2025, FEE ITEMS 13070 & 13075 ARE AMENDED AS FOLLOWS.
"IN OFFICE" IS REMOVED FROM THE FEE TITLES, AND NOTES ARE ADDED TO
INDICATE THESE SERVICES MAY BE PROVIDED IN-PERSON OR BY TELEHEALTH.
13070   ASSESSMENT OF AN UNRELATED CONDITION(S) IN ASSOCIATION WITH
        A WORKSAFEBC SERVICE
        NOTES:
        I)    PAID ONLY WHEN SERVICES ARE PROVIDED FOR AN UNRELATED
              ILLNESS OCCURRING IN CONJUNCTION WITH A WORKSAFEBC
              INSURED SERVICE.
        II)   UNRELATED SERVICE MUST BE INITIATED BY PATIENT.
        III)  THE UNRELATED CONDITION(S) MUST JUSTIFY A STAND-ALONE
              VISIT.
        IV)   ONLY PAID ONCE PER PATIENT PER DAY, PER INSURER, AND
              INCLUDES ALL OTHER UNRELATED PROBLEMS.
        V)    NOT PAID IF A PROCEDURE FOR THE SAME OR RELATED
              CONDITION IS PAID FOR SAME PATIENT ON SAME DAY, SAME
              PRACTITIONER.
        VI)   THE VISIT FOR EACH PAYER MUST BE FULLY AND ADEQUATELY
              DOCUMENTED IN CHART.
        VII)  PAID ONLY TO FAMILY PHYSICIANS.
        VIII) MAY BE PROVIDED IN-PERSON OR BY TELEHEALTH.
13075   ASSESSMENT OF AN UNRELATED CONDITION(S) IN ASSOCIATION WITH
        AN ICBC SERVICE
        NOTES:
        I)    PAID ONLY WHEN SERVICES ARE PROVIDED FOR AN UNRELATED
              ILLNESS OCCURRING IN CONJUNCTION WITH AN ICBC INSURED
              SERVICE.
        II)   UNRELATED SERVICE MUST BE INITIATED BY PATIENT.
        III)  THE UNRELATED CONDITION(S) MUST JUSTIFY A STAND-ALONE
              VISIT.
        IV)   ONLY PAID ONCE PER PATIENT PER DAY, PER INSURER, AND
              INCLUDES ALL OTHER UNRELATED PROBLEMS.
        V)    NOT PAID IF A PROCEDURE FOR THE SAME OR RELATED
              CONDITION IS PAID FOR SAME PATIENT ON SAME DAY, SAME
              PRACTITIONER.
        VI)   THE VISIT FOR EACH PAYER MUST BE FULLY AND ADEQUATELY
              DOCUMENTED IN CHART.
        VII)  PAID ONLY TO FAMILY PHYSICIANS.
        VIII) MAY BE PROVIDED IN-PERSON OR BY TELEHEALTH.
